1
00:00:01,020 --> 00:00:03,300
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:03,300 --> 00:00:08,610
Nirvana has started to move, and it's 
heading toward Wendy's guild, Caitshelter!

3
00:00:08,610 --> 00:00:09,280
Yes...

4
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:13,200
And we faced off against 
the Poison Dragon, Cobra!

5
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:13,990
Yes...!

6
00:00:13,990 --> 00:00:17,800
But you know, doesn't old man 
Jura kinda look like a potato?

7
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:19,280
I am not a potato!

8
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:55,880
I'm kinda... My body doesn't feel so...

9
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:57,850
Is it his poison?

10
00:02:00,790 --> 00:02:02,390
Damn it...

11
00:02:02,740 --> 00:02:05,290
I can't move... either...

12
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:14,940
Plus... I'm on transportation...

13
00:02:16,490 --> 00:02:21,680
By the pride of the Six 
Generals, I will defeat you!

14
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:27,120
Jura, the Tenth Saint!

15
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:32,780
Damn it... I can't move...

16
00:02:33,670 --> 00:02:44,790
I can hear it... I can hear the end of the 
life of an Old Generation Dragon Slayer!

17
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:57,080
Enough, Cobra.

18
00:02:57,480 --> 00:03:00,420
B-Brain?

19
00:03:00,420 --> 00:03:01,950
What are you...

20
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,360
You did well.

21
00:03:04,990 --> 00:03:06,740
Rest in peace.

22
00:03:08,790 --> 00:03:12,500
In the end, nothing more 
than a fake Dragon Slayer...

23
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:16,340
I have no need for him as one of the six 
generals that will crush the official guilds.

24
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:18,340
Trash!

25
00:03:18,810 --> 00:03:21,840
Oops. Did you hear that?

26
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:27,700
Damn you...

27
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,650
Damn you!

28
00:03:32,510 --> 00:03:34,860
My prayer...

29
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:41,740
I only wanted to hear the 
voice of my one friend...

30
00:03:44,780 --> 00:03:46,580
Cubellios...

31
00:03:55,490 --> 00:03:56,610
Cobra...

32
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:05,190
Weren't you... his ally?

33
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:11,300
Ally? I can gather as many as I wish shortly.

34
00:04:11,550 --> 00:04:13,890
Using Nirvana's power, that is.

35
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:17,400
You can't call those allies.

36
00:04:18,270 --> 00:04:20,330
They're just puppets!

37
00:04:20,610 --> 00:04:22,610
Now, now... Don't get testy.

38
00:04:23,150 --> 00:04:26,540
I have taken an interest in your power.

39
00:04:27,620 --> 00:04:30,290
I suspect you know what I mean by that.

40
00:04:32,860 --> 00:04:36,870
I will make you my first puppet slave!

41
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:51,810
I... lost?

42
00:04:52,230 --> 00:04:55,030
Those with the stronger ideals will win!

43
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:58,800
That is what Jura said!

44
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:02,350
No... I don't wanna lose...

45
00:05:03,430 --> 00:05:06,240
If I lose, then Father will abandon me...

46
00:05:07,860 --> 00:05:09,310
I don't wanna lose!

47
00:05:12,530 --> 00:05:14,290
Running is futile!

48
00:05:14,650 --> 00:05:15,660
Yes...!

49
00:05:16,990 --> 00:05:21,500
My Heaven's Eye can see through everything!

50
00:05:23,380 --> 00:05:24,010
I have seen!

51
00:05:24,660 --> 00:05:26,540
Liquid Ground!

52
00:05:42,890 --> 00:05:46,430
At this rate, I'm going to be abandoned...

53
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:50,780
Father... will abandon me!

54
00:05:51,050 --> 00:05:54,370
That may be for the best, yes?

55
00:05:58,390 --> 00:06:03,020
Today, Oracion Seis will be no more!

56
00:06:14,300 --> 00:06:15,140
There he is!

57
00:06:16,510 --> 00:06:17,450
Natsu!

58
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:20,320
What happened?

59
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:24,150
It's 'cause this is transportation...

60
00:06:28,110 --> 00:06:29,840
Everyone...

61
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:30,680
Happy!

62
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,720
Cat-dono, you are also unharmed?

63
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,330
Cat-dono?

64
00:06:35,690 --> 00:06:37,830
Save Natsu...

65
00:06:37,830 --> 00:06:39,580
He's being taken away...

66
00:06:40,540 --> 00:06:43,360
Half of the Six Generals are finished.

67
00:06:44,070 --> 00:06:45,460
Their stars have fallen.

68
00:06:47,780 --> 00:06:51,010
Starting now, I will create 
a new set of Generals.

69
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:54,010
Including this one.

70
00:06:58,300 --> 00:07:04,690
I figured this would happen eventually. 
Finally getting scouted by a Dark Guild, huh?

71
00:07:04,690 --> 00:07:08,850
Natsu isn't gonna do what you say!

72
00:07:09,350 --> 00:07:13,520
Nirvana will soak this 
boy's heart in darkness,

73
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:16,080
and he will become nothing 
but my loyal servant.

74
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,680
Hell no, I won't!

75
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:23,710
You still have that much strength left?

76
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:33,370
He does not seem so well.

77
00:07:33,370 --> 00:07:36,860
He gets extreme motion sickness.

78
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:44,630
Hurry up... and beat... this guy...

79
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:47,790
Stop... this thing...

80
00:07:48,980 --> 00:07:52,250
I'm not doin' it for you, but sure.

81
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:53,150
Yeah!

82
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:55,390
Stop?

83
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,780
Nirvana?

84
00:07:59,140 --> 00:08:01,040
Not even possible.

85
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:10,460
This city will shortly reach 
its first destination.

86
00:08:12,730 --> 00:08:15,590
We will arrive at Caitshelter.

87
00:08:17,180 --> 00:08:20,070
That's Wendy and Carla's guild!

88
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,590
But why?

89
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:28,940
Tell us your purpose. Why do 
you aim for Wendy-dono's guild?

90
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:36,840
This ultra-inversion magic can change a 
guild of light into one of darkness in an instant.

91
00:08:37,790 --> 00:08:39,370
I can't wait.

92
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:43,080
I suspect you'll see true hell.

93
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:44,950
We can't let this guy off!

94
00:08:44,950 --> 00:08:47,130
This bastard is gettin' to me!

95
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:52,240
Did you not hear me?

96
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:55,010
Tell us your purpose!

97
00:08:59,130 --> 00:09:03,380
I have no words for pitiful 
weaklings like you!

98
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:07,210
I will become the judge ruling 
over light and darkness!

99
00:09:07,210 --> 00:09:08,690
Bow down before me!

100
00:09:09,140 --> 00:09:11,170
This man needs to be dealt with.

101
00:09:11,170 --> 00:09:12,050
Dude...

102
00:09:12,050 --> 00:09:15,370
It seems like there is no talking with him.

103
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:19,820
Begone, worms!

104
00:09:40,530 --> 00:09:44,100
W-What is this magic power?

105
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:51,560
Stand. I will not let you rest until you 
say why you are targeting Caitshelter.

106
00:09:57,800 --> 00:10:00,910
Wait, could this old guy...

107
00:10:01,180 --> 00:10:03,430
...be really crazy powerful?

108
00:10:27,100 --> 00:10:31,540
This is someone with the title of 
Wizard Saint, just like our master.

109
00:10:35,270 --> 00:10:39,260
I see... You surprised me for a moment there.

110
00:10:39,260 --> 00:10:43,240
I suppose the distinction of being one of 
the Wizard Saints is not just for show.

111
00:10:43,730 --> 00:10:47,950
There are many other guilds 
closer than Caitshelter.

112
00:10:47,950 --> 00:10:53,940
There must be some reason why 
you head there specifically.

113
00:10:59,540 --> 00:11:03,590
There is no need for those that 
will shortly be dead to know!

114
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:06,970
Dark Rondo!

115
00:11:27,110 --> 00:11:28,830
Rockiron Wall!

116
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:34,130
Whoa! That's amazing! And 
actually kinda scary...

117
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:42,830
Do you understand how 
futile this battle is now?

118
00:11:42,830 --> 00:11:45,780
Tell me the reason you aim for Caitshelter.

119
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:48,390
And what will you do if you know?

120
00:11:53,140 --> 00:11:55,500
I said it was futile!

121
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,400
Oh, is that so?

122
00:12:00,950 --> 00:12:02,190
I have you now.

123
00:12:02,190 --> 00:12:03,420
Oh, no!

124
00:12:03,420 --> 00:12:05,030
Dude, behind you!

125
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:08,650
Dark Capriccio!

126
00:12:12,330 --> 00:12:13,870
The rocks are bending!

127
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:25,320
It's futile.

128
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:29,890
Dark Capriccio is a piercing magic.

129
00:12:29,890 --> 00:12:33,390
It will cut right through those damn rocks!

130
00:12:38,350 --> 00:12:41,030
The Rockiron Wall won't work against that!

131
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:44,280
He's got a way to pierce through,

132
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:46,950
but being able to dodge 
it is impressive, too!

133
00:12:46,950 --> 00:12:49,950
You should take back what you said before.

134
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:52,830
It is not futile.

135
00:12:53,950 --> 00:12:59,250
Now, what will you do, Wizard Saint?

136
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:03,800
Dark Capriccio!

137
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:06,020
Rockiron Wall!

138
00:13:08,710 --> 00:13:10,710
The same thing again?

139
00:13:10,710 --> 00:13:12,640
Perhaps that's what is futile!

140
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:19,980
My Dark Capriccio will 
eventually turn you to dust!

141
00:13:19,980 --> 00:13:22,130
That would be good if it were true.

142
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:31,650
I will finish this. And in a big way!

143
00:13:31,950 --> 00:13:34,810
Dark Capriccio Scream!

144
00:13:36,710 --> 00:13:39,090
Rockiron Wall Continuous Chain!

145
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:45,130
Jura, run!

146
00:14:11,590 --> 00:14:13,700
He's trapped in rocks.

147
00:14:15,640 --> 00:14:17,250
Supreme Rock Shatter!

148
00:14:24,340 --> 00:14:30,330
Even while withstanding such fierce attacks, he 
noticed he could use the shattered pieces of rocks!

149
00:14:32,260 --> 00:14:35,310
No wonder even Lyon treats him with respect.

150
00:14:38,940 --> 00:14:43,150
Heck yeah! That guy's the 
boss of Oracion Seis, right?

151
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:46,490
We won!

152
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:53,980
Now... Tell me the reason you are 
aiming for Wendy-dono's guild.

153
00:14:54,650 --> 00:14:58,580
Wait, shouldn't we just stop it?

154
00:14:58,830 --> 00:15:02,000
Do it for me, please...

155
00:15:03,530 --> 00:15:09,630
I cannot believe that I... was... defeated...

156
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:15,250
Midnight... I leave the rest to you.

157
00:15:16,140 --> 00:15:19,480
The Six Generals will never be defeated.

158
00:15:20,330 --> 00:15:23,520
When the six prayers vanish,

159
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:26,630
he will...

160
00:15:31,380 --> 00:15:33,110
"He?"

161
00:15:33,110 --> 00:15:39,360
And hey, didn't one of those symbols 
on his face just disappear?

162
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:42,810
Please don't freak me out like that.

163
00:15:42,810 --> 00:15:45,070
I'm gonna have nightmares about this now!

164
00:15:45,630 --> 00:15:47,320
Everyone!

165
00:15:48,970 --> 00:15:50,170
Wendy!

166
00:15:50,940 --> 00:15:54,470
I figured that all that 
ruckus was you people.

167
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:57,160
Carla!

168
00:15:58,500 --> 00:15:59,930
This city...

169
00:16:00,230 --> 00:16:03,600
I think it might be heading toward our guild!

170
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:06,030
Seems like it. But don't worry now.

171
00:16:09,680 --> 00:16:12,730
The snake charmer's defeated over there.

172
00:16:16,060 --> 00:16:17,070
Then...

173
00:16:17,570 --> 00:16:22,340
It's probably Brain here that 
was manipulating Nirvana.

174
00:16:22,630 --> 00:16:26,700
So since we defeated him, 
the city should stop, right?

175
00:16:27,980 --> 00:16:29,910
I don't like this.

176
00:16:29,910 --> 00:16:34,220
In the end, we never found out why 
he was heading for Caitshelter.

177
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:37,590
Maybe there wasn't any 
particular reason for it.

178
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:42,910
When the six prayers vanish,

179
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:46,090
he will...

180
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:54,080
There are still some things left 
unsolved, but it is over now.

181
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:57,290
No, it ain't!

182
00:16:59,790 --> 00:17:02,910
Hurry up and stop this thing!

183
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:06,130
Natsu-san!

184
00:17:06,470 --> 00:17:08,480
Is he poisoned?

185
00:17:11,170 --> 00:17:13,110
The he-cat, too!

186
00:17:13,110 --> 00:17:15,150
You are so pitiful.

187
00:17:15,150 --> 00:17:16,590
Aye...

188
00:17:19,590 --> 00:17:20,880
I...

189
00:17:22,650 --> 00:17:23,910
I...

190
00:17:25,050 --> 00:17:26,210
...am dreaming.

191
00:17:32,780 --> 00:17:34,440
You are also dreaming.

192
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:39,030
In the dead of night...

193
00:17:53,380 --> 00:17:59,210
Magic cannot hit me.

194
00:17:59,890 --> 00:18:02,600
Midnight isn't even injured?

195
00:18:04,210 --> 00:18:09,350
I've surpassed my father 
as the strongest wizard.

196
00:18:15,150 --> 00:18:16,960
My prayer...

197
00:18:18,910 --> 00:18:20,520
My brother!

198
00:18:21,260 --> 00:18:27,130
I wanted to see your face, one more time...

199
00:18:34,730 --> 00:18:37,420
Five prayers have vanished.

200
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:42,680
Midnight... Do not vanish, no matter what.

201
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:46,120
<i>That</i> is my prayer.

202
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:05,850
What the hell?

203
00:19:06,170 --> 00:19:07,650
What in the world...?

204
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:12,680
There's nothing that looks 
like controls at all!

205
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:15,890
Then, how can we stop it?

206
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,010
Damn it!

207
00:19:28,990 --> 00:19:33,380
I thought it would stop 
if we defeated Brain...

208
00:19:33,380 --> 00:19:36,830
We were naive! Now we have 
no idea how to stop it!

209
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:44,030
What should I do? I cast a spell 
to cure poison, but he's still...

210
00:19:44,650 --> 00:19:47,280
Natsu can't handle transportation.

211
00:19:47,530 --> 00:19:49,330
So pitiful!

212
00:19:51,380 --> 00:19:53,700
I'm gonna hurl...

213
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:55,270
Motion sickness?

214
00:19:55,270 --> 00:19:56,360
Aye!

215
00:19:56,360 --> 00:19:57,040
In that case...

216
00:19:58,470 --> 00:20:01,860
Maybe a spell to cure his sense 
of equilibrium will work.

217
00:20:02,230 --> 00:20:03,130
Troia.

218
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:08,680
I'm baaack!

219
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:10,700
Fine! Totally fine!

220
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:12,150
Thank goodness.

221
00:20:12,150 --> 00:20:13,440
I'm glad it worked.

222
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:16,120
You rock, Wendy!

223
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:18,100
Please teach me that magic!

224
00:20:18,670 --> 00:20:21,570
It's Sky Magic... That's impossible.

225
00:20:21,850 --> 00:20:25,540
This doesn't feel like transportation at all!

226
00:20:25,950 --> 00:20:30,080
Okay! Lucy, summon a boat or train Spirit!

227
00:20:30,410 --> 00:20:32,350
I don't have one like that!

228
00:20:32,350 --> 00:20:35,150
And anyway, this isn't the time!

229
00:20:35,150 --> 00:20:36,630
Get with the picture, would ya?

230
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:42,880
We don't know how to stop it. As 
you can see, there's nothing here.

231
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:52,570
But Hot Eye... I mean, Richard, said that 
this was the place it was controlled from.

232
00:20:54,140 --> 00:20:57,130
I do not believe that Richard-dono would lie.

233
00:20:57,620 --> 00:21:00,340
Besides having it stop or not,

234
00:21:00,340 --> 00:21:04,080
hasn't anyone noticed something 
even more peculiar?

235
00:21:05,780 --> 00:21:09,330
There's no controls, and no 
one here in the King's Summit.

236
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,240
Brain has been defeated.

237
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:16,210
So why is it still moving?

238
00:21:16,210 --> 00:21:18,710
Could it be operating on auto-pilot?

239
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:22,230
Nirvana has already been set to fire!

240
00:21:33,420 --> 00:21:37,440
Our... guild...

241
00:21:39,950 --> 00:21:41,230
Don't worry.

242
00:21:41,850 --> 00:21:43,730
Your guild ain't goin' anywhere.

243
00:21:44,610 --> 00:21:46,390
Let me do you this favor.

244
00:21:48,610 --> 00:21:50,900
I'll stop it, no matter what.

245
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:15,850
Nirvana will not stop.

246
00:22:17,340 --> 00:22:19,730
As long as I am here.

247
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:59,900
Natsu, you don't really bring the 
"gravitas" when you talk, you know?

248
00:23:59,900 --> 00:24:02,520
What? I say cool stuff all the time!

249
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:03,700
Like what?

250
00:24:03,980 --> 00:24:06,320
Uh, oh yeah, that!

251
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,380
Like "I'm all fired up!" and stuff.

252
00:24:08,380 --> 00:24:11,350
"Let's do this!" Stuff like that.

253
00:24:11,350 --> 00:24:13,470
That's just your catch phrases!

254
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:16,430
Next time: It is Your Words

255
00:24:16,430 --> 00:24:20,250
I meant words that people 
remember in their hearts!

256
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:22,060
"I'll kick your ass!" Yeah, I guess not.

257
00:24:22,060 --> 00:24:24,560
All people will remember 
from that is the trauma.

258
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:26,660


